  "title": "Spurious emission",
  "parse": {
    "text": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>4-1-070</b>\n</p><p>Emission on a frequency or frequencies which are outside the necessary band, and the level of which may be reduced without affecting the corresponding transmission of information. Spurious emissions include harmonic emissions, parasitic emissions and intermodulation products, but exclude emissions in the immediate vicinity of the necessary band, which are a result of the modulation process for the transmission of information.\n</p><p>Reference: <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"dd7536794b63bf90eccfd37f9b147d7f\">I</span>.<span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"b9ece18c950afbfa6b0fdbfa4ff731d3\">T</span>.U.\n</p><p><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<i>Please note that this is the term as it stands in the original <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\">IALA</span> Dictionary edition (1970-1989)</i>\n<br>\n</p>\n<div class=\"LanguageLinks\">\n<table width=\"100%\">\n<tbody><tr valign=\"top\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF\">\n<td style=\"width: 25px; padding-left: 0em; border-right: 1px solid #aaaaaa;border-left: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-top: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-bottom: 1px solid #EEF3E2;\"><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:25px-Geographylogo.png\" class=\"mw-file-description\" title=\"Languages\"><img alt=\"Languages\" src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/8/82/25px-Geographylogo.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" class=\"mw-file-element\"></a></span></td>\n<td style=\"padding: 1px 1em 0; background: #EEF3E2;\">\n<p><b><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">English</a></b>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"dd7536794b63bf90eccfd37f9b147d7f\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>charge current\n</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Intensity\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"b9ece18c950afbfa6b0fdbfa4ff731d3\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Time period\n</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>roll period\n</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Transmissivity\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities - AISM\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260615233235\nCache expiry: 86400\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: []\nCPU time usage: 0.044 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.052 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 60/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 786/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 229/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/100\nExpensive parser function count: 4/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   15.749      1 -total\n 71.66%   11.285      1 Template:Languages\n 48.34%    7.613      4 Template:Languages/Lang\n 27.14%    4.274      1 Template:IALAFooter\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key wiki_iala_dictionary_1_41:pcache:idhash:917-0!canonical and timestamp 20260615233235 and revision id 2769. Rendering was triggered because: page-view\n -->\n</div>",
